'''Tekkatho''' ({{IPA2|t蓻虁蕯g脿d貌}}) means [[university]] in [[Burmese language]], which derives from the name [[Taxila|Taxila University]], located in modern-day [[Pakistan]]. In colonial times, [[writer]]s, [[artist]]s, and [[photographer]]s who had studied at university used Tekkatho as a title in front of their [[penname]]s.

